The paper deals with video object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses an external memory to store and retrieve information, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper uses a dataset and a benchmark to evaluate the proposed approach, which falls under the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with tracking objects in motion, which is a problem in robotics and control systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category as well.
